quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
15,1,"Alif. Lam. Ra'. These are the verses of the Book, and a Clear Qur'an. {1}",footnotes:1:This verse is the brief introduction to the Surah
15,2,"Soon will the time come when the unbelievers will wish they were Muslims."
15,3,"Leave them to eat and enjoy life and let false hopes amuse them. They will soon come to know."
15,4,"Whenever We destroyed a town, a definite term had previously been decreed for it. {1}",footnotes:1:This is to refute the fallacious argument of the disbelievers that Muhammad (peace be upon him) was not a true Prophet because they had received no prompt punishment for their disbelief. It is like this: We have never seized a community at the first committal of kufr.
15,5,"No people can outstrip the term for its destruction nor can it delay it."
15,6,"They say: "O you to whom the Admonition<sup foot_note="178626">1</sup> has been revealed, you are surely crazed.",footnotes:178626:The word zikr literally means “to cause to remember”,"“to caution” and “to give advice”. But the Quran has used it as a technical term for “admonition”", which comes as a precept. Thus all the Books that had been sent down to the Messengers were zikr, and the Quran is also zikr.
  15,7,"Why do you not bring down angels upon us if you are indeed truthful?""
15,8,"We do not send down the angels (in frivolity); and when We do send them down, {1} We do so with Truth; then people are granted no respite. {2}",footnotes:1:“We do not send down the angels.” We do not send down the angels for the mere fun of it in response to the request of the people
15,9,"As for the Admonition, indeed it is We Who have revealed it and it is indeed We Who are its guardians. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
15,10,"(O Muhammad), certainly We did send Messengers before you among the nations which have gone by."
15,11,"And whenever a Messenger came to them, they never failed to mock him."
15,12,"Even so We make a way for it (that is, the Admonition) in the hearts of the culprits (like a hot rod);"
15,13,"they do not believe in it. {1} This has been the wont of people of this kind from ancient times.",footnotes:1:The majority of the translators and commentators are of the opinion that the pronoun “it”( Ayat 12)
15,14,"If We were even to open for them a way to the heavens, and they could continually climb up to it in broad daylight,"
15,15,"they would still have said: "Surely our eyes have been dazzled; rather, we have been enchanted.""
